OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F395A1773857158
OL,3,CNine places across UK to battle it out
OL,4,Cfor UK City of Culture title
OL,6,F"Blackpool is bursting with culture
OL,7,Fand variety. We've just celebrated a
OL,8,Fweek-long festival of circus and magic
OL,9,Fand are looking forward to welcoming
OL,10,Fthe works of both Claude Monet and
OL,11,FWilliam Shakespeare in March - all of
OL,12,Fwhich is complemented by our year-
OL,13,Fround celebration of the art and
OL,14,Fculture of today and tomorrow. "Our
OL,15,Fdiverse culture and entertainment
OL,16,Foffer means Blackpool has something
OL,17,Ffor everybody, from all age groups and
OL,18,Fbackgrounds. Being named as the City
OL,19,Fof Culture 2029 would showcase the
OL,20,Ftalent and creativity that we already
OL,21,Fhave on our doorstep, making all our
OL,22,Fresidents proud of our bold, vibrant
OL,23,Fand cultural town. "To top it all off,
OL,24,F2029 would mark the 150th anniversary
OL,25,Fof one of Britain's first and most
OL,26,Floved mass arts displays ` the
OL,26,@nD@AOUvD@`OUCE@YO]
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G4/11
